African Rainbow’s Motsepe Is South Africa’s Richest, Times Says

-- B y   R e n e e   B o n o r c h i s
-- 
2011-09-04T07:32:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-04/african-rainbow-s-motsepe-is-south-africa-s-richest-times-says.html
African Rainbow Mineral Ltd.’s
founder and Chairman Patrice Motsepe is the richest man in  South
Africa  and worth 22.99 billion rand ($3.26 billion), the  Sunday
Times  said, citing the annual wealth survey carried out by
research company Who Owns Whom.  Lakshmi Mittal of  ArcelorMittal South Africa Ltd. (ACL)  is the
second-wealthiest person worth 20.87 billion rand, the
Johannesburg-based weekly newspaper said, based on the survey’s
results. There were 28 billionaires in South Africa as of March
31, compared to 31 the year before, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Renee Bonorchis in Johannesburg at 
